<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4547260>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIG. 6. — Armatoglyptes flexuosus n. sp., dwarf males at different stages: A, just settled cyprid of dwarf male; B, posterior part of carapace of settled cyprid; C, cypris antennules; D, newly developed dwarf male, in prior to shed off cypris carapace; E, posterior part of shed carapace; F, posterior lattice organs (3rd and 4th pairs) on carapace surface; G, young, immature male; H, posterior end of immature dwarf male with apertural slit; I, attachment antennule of dwarf male; J, mature dwarf male; K, posterior end of mature dwarf male with apertural slit; L, surface of cuticle at posterior end of dwarf male,showing circular striation.Abbreviations:as, apertural slit; AS2, AS3, AS4, 2nd, 3rd and 4th segments of cypris antennule; LO 3-4, posterior lattice organs 3 and 4. Scale bars: A, D, G, J, 10 μm; B, C, F, 3 μm; E, H, I, K, L, 5 μm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4547260/files/figure.png" .

